<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 15 at 12:26AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Areas of Fog Developing across Cameron County...
Surface observations and satellite data indicate that areas of
fog are quickly developing across portions of Cameron County
tonight. Some areas of locally dense fog are reducing visibilities
of around 1/4 of a mile, mainly in the Brownsville and Harlingen
areas. A Dense Fog Advisory may be needed for portions of Deep
South Texas overnight into Tuesday morning
Late night motorists in the Brownsville and Harlingen areas are
urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and avoid
following other vehicles too closely in the areas of denser fog
through the overnight and early morning hours.</description>
